<paragraph blockId="60.[212,1444,855,1018]" pageId="60" pageNumber="159">
DESCRIPTION. — Male: humeral area in dorsal view concavely curved (sinuous). Flattening or depression of the elytral dorsum to the sides ends normally with stria 7, not with 5 or 6 as in 
<emphasis box="[1015,1265,891,914]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="159">
<taxonomicName box="[1015,1128,891,914]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Celeuthetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">P. insularis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1139,1265,891,914]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platysimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planidorsi">P. planidorsi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
