<taxonomicName box="[1318,1406,891,914]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platysimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setiger">
<emphasis box="[1318,1406,891,914]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="159">P. setiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[212,1444,855,1018]" pageId="60" pageNumber="159">
Female: subparallel sides of elytra and a non-excavate ventrite 5 separates 
<taxonomicName box="[1041,1205,925,949]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platysimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septentionalis">
<emphasis box="[1041,1205,925,949]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="159">P. septentionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<emphasis box="[1271,1401,925,949]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="159">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Paulian" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[1271,1397,925,949]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platysimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fleutiauxi">P. fleutiauxi</taxonomicName>
