<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="159" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="60.[212,1444,1479,1538]" box="[212,1444,1479,1503]" pageId="60" pageNumber="159">ETYMOLOGY. — The Latin epithet ‘septentrionális’, meaning northerly, came from ‘septentrio’ (pl. septentriones) for</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[212,1444,1479,1538]" box="[212,1187,1514,1538]" pageId="60" pageNumber="159">
the seven brightest stars of 
<taxonomicName box="[502,617,1515,1538]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ursa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="60" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis box="[502,617,1515,1538]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="159">Ursa major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the Great Bear Constellation right by the north pole.
</paragraph>
